The paper deals with sublinear algorithms for property testing of probability distributions, which involves sampling and querying subsets of the domain. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as statistical inference (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.SI.
